Executive Profile
Stacey S. Rauch  Non-Executive Chairman, Fiesta Restaurant Group, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships59$152,527
Background

		Ms. Stacey S. Rauch was a Senior Partner of McKinsey & Company from 1998 to 2010. Ms. Rauch served as a Leader in McKinsey's Retail and Consumer Goods Practices from 2006 to 2008 and served as its Head of the North American Retail and acted as the Global Retail Practice Convener. She led McKinsey's North American Retail Practice from 2001 to 2008. She was the first woman to be appointed as an Industry Practice Leader at McKinsey. During her tenure, she developed substantial ... expertise working with specialty retailers, wholesale apparel manufacturers and department stores and also acquired extensive experience in other areas of the retail sector including grocery retail, consumer packaged goods and big-box hard goods retail. She is a 24 year veteran of McKinsey. She served at McKinsey & Company from 1986 to September 2010. Prior to McKinsey, she spent 5 years in product management for General Foods Corporation. Ms. Rauch serves as Director Emeritus of McKinsey & Company from which she retired in September 2010. She has been the Non-Executive Chairman at Fiesta Restaurant Group, Inc. since February 27, 2017. She has been a Director at CEB Inc. since November 7, 2014; Fiesta Restaurant Group, Inc. since June 2012; AnnTaylor Stores Corp. since January 26, 2011; and Ascena Retail Group, Inc. since June 8, 2017. She serves as a Director Emeritus of McKinsey. She has been Non-Executive Director at Land Securities Group Plc since January 1, 2012. She served as a Director of Tops Holding II Corporation since October 14, 2010 and ANN Inc. from January 26, 2011 to August 21, 2015. Ms. Rauch holds a BS in Economics and an M.B.A. from The Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania.Read Full Background




